ChatGPT:

Unable to download Mustache.js file from CDN [duplicate]
stackoverflow.com
Certainly! You can download the latest version of Mustache.js directly from its official GitHub repository:

Visit the GitHub Releases Page: Navigate to the Mustache.js Releases section on GitHub. ​
GitHub

Download the Minified JavaScript File: Look for the latest release, and under the "Assets" section, you'll find mustache.min.js. Click on it to download the minified version suitable for production use.​

Include Mustache.js in Your Project: After downloading, place the mustache.min.js file in your project's directory (e.g., js/ folder). Then, include it in your HTML file as follows:​

html
Kopieren
Bearbeiten
<script src="js/mustache.min.js"></script>
This method ensures you have the latest version of Mustache.js running locally in your project.​



